albums.desc:
**Youkoso Japari Park e** *(Welcome to Japari Park)* is a single that was released on 2/8/2017. In addition to the titular opening theme of the [anime](https://japari-library.com/wiki/Kemono_Friends_(2017_Anime)), it also includes *[Oozora Dreamer](https://japari-library.com/wiki/Ozora_Dreamer)*, another song appearing in the series. In addition to the regular release, a limited edition single is also available. It includes an exclusive version of *Youkoso Japari Park e*, performed solely by [PPP](https://japari-library.com/wiki/PPP).

The song itself became popular in Japan back in 2017 and it became playable in various arcade rhythm games from 2017-2020. This song even reached as one of the top songs in Japanese Music Hit Charts. Because of its popularity, more versions of *Youkoso Japari Park e* are featured in future *Kemono Friends* albums. A special version known as *"[Tadaima](https://japari-library.com/wiki/S2E12:_I%27m_Home) Ver."* can be found on *"Youkoso Japari Park e ~The Complete Best~"*, a special album featuring a CD full of every version of this song including Masayoshi Oishi's Cover as a bonus track, and a DVD featuring all live performances of this song as well as bonus content about this song.

It contains a new version of the series' opening theme, Ozora Dreamer, three original songs and a handful of short songs performed by characters (e.g. [[Crested Ibis/Anime|Crested Ibis]]) during the anime. albums.desc: '''Japari CafÃ© 2''', released 12/13/2017, is a character song album for the [[Kemono Friends (2017 Anime)|Kemono Friends anime]]. It contains seven original songs and the Kemono Friends version of 40mP's Do Re Mi Fa Rondo. The physical release of the album also contained piano sheet music for [[Fre! Fre! Best Friends]].

'''PPP in the Sky!''', released 4/25/2018, is the major debut album of  [[PPP]]. It contains [[Jyunjyou Fripper|Junjou Flipper]], the main theme of [[Kemono Friends Festival]]. In addition to PPP's previously released original songs, it also includes eight new original songs (three unit songs and five solo songs for each member) and one cover song. The limited edition version of the album was also released on the same day. It includes five solo versions of Youkoso Japari Park e, performed by each PPP member.
